refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
booltouch stringfilename intnullmtime&null; intnullatime&null;
Attempts to set the access and modification times of the file named in the filename parameter to the value given in mtime. Note that the access time is always modified, regardless of the number of parameters.
If the file does not exist, it will be created.

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    8.0.0

     mtime and atime
     are now nullable.

  &reftitle.examples;



    touch example


<?php
if (touch($filename)) {
    echo $filename . ' modification time has been changed to present time';
} else {
    echo 'Sorry, could not change modification time of ' . $filename;
}
?>







    touch using the mtime parameter


<?php
// This is the touch time, we'll set it to one hour in the past.
$time = time() - 3600;

// Touch the file
if (!touch('some_file.txt', $time)) {
    echo 'Whoops, something went wrong...';
} else {
    echo 'Touched file with success';
}
?>
